Fulton County Superior Court Judge Jerry Baxter called the cheating scandal 'the sickest thing that's ever happened in this town' All but one of 10 former Atlanta public school educators convicted in a widespread conspiracy to inflate student scores on standardized tests were sentenced on Tuesday . 
  Former teacher Pamela Cleveland was the only one of the accused to take a plea deal and was sentenced to 5 years probation . 
  The three former SRT directors were sentenced to seven years in prison, 13 years probation and a $25,000 fine . 
  Former testing coordinator Donald Bullock was also sentenced to five years in jail . 
  Judge Baxter said the cheating was 'pervasive' and 'sickest thing' he had seen in Atlanta . 
 